{"id": 223714512, "title": "Could Kevin De Bruyne Depart Manchester City This Summer?", "text": "Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Share to Linkedin LONDON, ENGLAND - MAY 25: Kevin De Bruyne of Manchester City during the Emirates FA Cup Final match ... [+] between Manchester City and Manchester United at Wembley Stadium on May 25, 2024 in London, England. (Photo by Robin Jones/Getty Images) Getty Images With Manchester City trailing in Saturday\u2019s FA Cup final, Kevin de Bruyne was withdrawn with just over half an hour left to play. The Belgian had struggled to make much of an impression on the match and watched from the bench as Manchester United claimed a shock victory over the closest rivals. This came against a backdrop of much speculation about de Bruyne\u2019s future. The midfielder has reportedly spoken to clubs in the Saudi Pro League over a summer transfer with MLS expansion franchise San Diego FC also believed to be interested in the 32-year-old. De Bruyne is facing a career crossroads. While Pep Guardiola substituted de Bruyne before the end of Saturday\u2019s FA Cup final, the Belgian was still an important figure for City this season. The midfielder contributed six goals and 11 assists in 25 appearances in all competitions and was missed in the period he was injured. Guardiola clearly rates de Bruyne highly. MANCHESTER, ENGLAND - MAY 19: Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola celebrates with Phil Foden after ... [+] the Premier League match between Manchester City and West Ham United at Etihad Stadium on May 19, 2024 in Manchester, England.(Photo by Visionhaus/Getty Images) Visionhaus/Getty Images However, de Bruyne will turn 33 this summer and is into the twilight of his career. Manchester City has a good track record of judging when to move on key players - see Sergio Aguero, David Silva and Vincent Kompany - and it might be time for the Premier Premier League champions to consider bidding farewell to de Bruyne. MORE FOR YOU The Best Beers In Canada According To The Canadian Brewing Awards The 83 Best Memorial Day Sales According To Our Deal Savvy Editors NYT Strands 84 Hints Spangram And Answers For Sunday May 26th After all, City already has Phil Foden to step into de Bruyne\u2019s position. This transition might have already happened with Foden the biggest driving force behind Manchester City\u2019s Premier League-winning campaign. The England international was so impressive he might even be a Ballon d\u2019Or candidate this year. On his day, de Bruyne is still one of the best midfielders in the Premier League. He might be the best passer English soccer has even seen with de Bruyne\u2019s range with the ball at his feet key to the way Manchester City plays. The problem is that the 32-year-old is suffering an increasing number of injuries. LONDON, ENGLAND - MAY 14: Kevin De Bruyne of Manchester City beats a tackle from Radu Dragusin of ... [+] Tottenham Hotspur during the Premier League match between Tottenham Hotspur and Manchester City at Tottenham Hotspur Stadium on May 14, 2024 in London, England. (Photo by James Gill - Danehouse/Getty Images) Getty Images De Bruyne has missed several matches through injury in each of the last two seasons. Guardiola was able to keep City moving forwards by repurposing Julian Alvarez as a number 10 and deploying Foden in a central role. Would, however, Guardiola prefer that the money paid to de Bruyne be reinvested in a different area of his squad? Despite defeat to Manchester United on Saturday, City is the dominant force in English soccer right now and it has earned this position through good decisions over a number of years. Some of those decisions have been difficult ones and the Etihad Stadium club faces another one over the future of arguably its greatest-ever player. Graham Ruthven Following Editorial Standards Print Reprints & Permissions", "summary": "Kevin de Bruyne has been linked with a transfer to the Saudi Pro League and MLS after Manchester City's FA Cup f